# @exchange/shared Conventions

Spec: `openspec/specs/shared-contracts/spec.md`, `design-system-standards/spec.md`

## Purpose

Single source of truth for contracts used by both `apps/web` and `apps/api`.

## What belongs here

- Domain types (`Order`, `Balance`, `Ticker`, …)
- Enums (`OrderSide`, `OrderStatus`, `ErrorCode`, `WsChannel`, …)
- API DTOs (`PlaceOrderDto`, `LoginDto`, …)
- WebSocket event types (discriminated unions in `ws-events.ts`)
- Trading pair config (`TRADING_PAIRS`, `getTradingPair`)
- Number formatters (`format/number.ts`)
- Theme tokens (`COLOR_CONVENTION`, `SEMANTIC_COLORS`)
- Decimal utilities (`decimal.ts`)

## What does NOT belong here

- React components (keep in `apps/web`)
- NestJS services or Prisma code (keep in `apps/api`)

## Implementation rules

- Export everything from `src/index.ts`
- Use `decimal.js` for all formatter/calculation logic
- API transmits raw amounts as `string`; formatters handle display
- After changes, run `pnpm --filter @exchange/shared build`
- Keep `package.json` exports with `import`, `require`, and `default` for tsx/Node compatibility
